31void testInsertSignedBitfieldInZero32()
32{
33 if (JSC::Options::defaultB3OptLevel() < 2)
34 return;
35 int32_t src = 0xffffffff;
36 Vector<int32_t> lsbs = { 1, 14, 29 };
37 Vector<int32_t> widths = { 30, 17, 2 };
38
39 // Test Pattern: (((src & mask1) ^ mask2) - mask2) << lsb
40 // where: mask1 = (1 << width) - 1
41 // mask2 = 1 << (width - 1)
42 auto test = [&] (int32_t lsb, int32_t mask1, int32_t mask2) -> int32_t {
43 Procedure proc;
44 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
45
46 Value* srcValue = root->appendNew<Value>(
47 proc, Trunc, Origin(),
48 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0));
49 Value* lsbValue = root->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), lsb);
50 Value* mask1Value = root->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), mask1);
51 Value* mask2Value = root->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), mask2);
52
53 Value* andValue = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitAnd, Origin(), srcValue, mask1Value);
54 Value* xorValue = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitXor, Origin(), andValue, mask2Value);
55 Value* subValue = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Sub, Origin(), xorValue, mask2Value);
56
57 root->appendNewControlValue(
58 proc, Return, Origin(),
59 root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Shl, Origin(), subValue, lsbValue));
60
61 auto code = compileProc(proc);
62 if (isARM64())
63 checkUsesInstruction(*code, "sbfiz");
64 return invoke<int32_t>(*code, src);
65 };
66
67 for (size_t i = 0; i < lsbs.size(); ++i) {
68 int32_t lsb = lsbs.at(i);
69 int32_t width = widths.at(i);
70 int32_t mask1 = (1 << width) - 1;
71 int32_t mask2 = 1 << (width - 1);
72 int32_t bfsx = ((src & mask1) ^ mask2) - mask2;
73 CHECK(test(lsb, mask1, mask2) == (bfsx << lsb));
74 }
75}
76
77void testInsertSignedBitfieldInZero64()
78{
79 if (JSC::Options::defaultB3OptLevel() < 2)
80 return;
81 int64_t src = 0xffffffffffffffff;
82 Vector<int64_t> lsbs = { 1, 30, 62 };
83 Vector<int64_t> widths = { 62, 33, 1 };
84
85 // Test Pattern: ((src << amount) >> amount) << lsb
86 // where: amount = datasize - width
87 auto test = [&] (int64_t lsb, int64_t amount) -> int64_t {
88 Procedure proc;
89 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
90
91 Value* srcValue = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0);
92 Value* lsbValue = root->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), lsb);
93 Value* amountValue = root->appendNew<Const64Value>(proc, Origin(), amount);
94
95 Value* signedRightShiftValue = root->appendNew<Value>(
96 proc, SShr, Origin(),
97 root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Shl, Origin(), srcValue, amountValue),
98 amountValue);
99
100 root->appendNewControlValue(
101 proc, Return, Origin(),
102 root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Shl, Origin(), signedRightShiftValue, lsbValue));
103
104 auto code = compileProc(proc);
105 if (isARM64())
106 checkUsesInstruction(*code, "sbfiz");
107 return invoke<uint64_t>(*code, src);
108 };
109
110 for (size_t i = 0; i < lsbs.size(); ++i) {
111 int64_t lsb = lsbs.at(i);
112 int64_t width = widths.at(i);
113 int64_t amount = CHAR_BIT * sizeof(src) - width;
114 int64_t bfsx = (src << amount) >> amount;
115 CHECK(test(lsb, amount) == (bfsx << lsb));
116 }
117}

119void testExtractSignedBitfield32()
120{
121 if (JSC::Options::defaultB3OptLevel() < 2)
122 return;
123 int32_t src = 0xffffffff;
124 Vector<int32_t> lsbs = { 1, 14, 29 };
125 Vector<int32_t> widths = { 30, 17, 2 };
126
127 // Test Pattern: (((src >> lsb) & mask1) ^ mask2) - mask2
128 // where: mask1 = (1 << width) - 1
129 // mask2 = 1 << (width - 1)
130 auto test = [&] (int32_t lsb, int32_t mask1, int32_t mask2) -> int32_t {
131 Procedure proc;
132 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
133
134 Value* srcValue = root->appendNew<Value>(
135 proc, Trunc, Origin(),
136 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0));
137 Value* lsbValue = root->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), lsb);
138 Value* mask1Value = root->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), mask1);
139 Value* mask2Value = root->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), mask2);
140
141 Value* shiftValue = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, SShr, Origin(), srcValue, lsbValue);
142 Value* andValue = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitAnd, Origin(), shiftValue, mask1Value);
143 Value* xorValue = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitXor, Origin(), andValue, mask2Value);
144
145 root->appendNewControlValue(
146 proc, Return, Origin(),
147 root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Sub, Origin(), xorValue, mask2Value));
148
149 auto code = compileProc(proc);
150 if (isARM64())
151 checkUsesInstruction(*code, "sbfx");
152 return invoke<int32_t>(*code, src);
153 };
154
155 for (size_t i = 0; i < lsbs.size(); ++i) {
156 int32_t lsb = lsbs.at(i);
157 int32_t width = widths.at(i);
158 int32_t mask1 = (1 << width) - 1;
159 int32_t mask2 = 1 << (width - 1);
160 int32_t result = (((src >> lsb) & mask1) ^ mask2) - mask2;
161 CHECK(test(lsb, mask1, mask2) == result);
162 }
163}

165void testExtractSignedBitfield64()
166{
167 if (JSC::Options::defaultB3OptLevel() < 2)
168 return;
169 int64_t src = 0xffffffffffffffff;
170 Vector<int64_t> lsbs = { 1, 30, 62 };
171 Vector<int64_t> widths = { 62, 33, 1 };
172
173 // Test Pattern: ((src >> lsb) << amount) >> amount
174 // where: amount = datasize - width
175 auto test = [&] (int64_t lsb, int64_t amount) -> int64_t {
176 Procedure proc;
177 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
178
179 Value* srcValue = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0);
180 Value* lsbValue = root->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), lsb);
181 Value* amountValue = root->appendNew<Const64Value>(proc, Origin(), amount);
182
183 Value* rightShiftValue = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, ZShr, Origin(), srcValue, lsbValue);
184 Value* leftShiftValue = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Shl, Origin(), rightShiftValue, amountValue);
185 Value* signedRightShiftValue = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, SShr, Origin(), leftShiftValue, amountValue);
186 root->appendNewControlValue(proc, Return, Origin(), signedRightShiftValue);
187
188 auto code = compileProc(proc);
189 if (isARM64())
190 checkUsesInstruction(*code, "sbfx");
191 return invoke<uint64_t>(*code, src);
192 };
193
194 for (size_t i = 0; i < lsbs.size(); ++i) {
195 int64_t lsb = lsbs.at(i);
196 int64_t width = widths.at(i);
197 int64_t amount = CHAR_BIT * sizeof(src) - width;
198 int64_t result = ((src >> lsb) << amount) >> amount;
199 CHECK(test(lsb, amount) == result);
200 }
201}

203void testBitOrBitOrArgImmImm32(int a, int b, int c)
204{
205 Procedure proc;
206 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
207 Value* innerBitOr = root->appendNew<Value>(
208 proc, BitOr, Origin(),
209 root->appendNew<Value>(
210 proc, Trunc, Origin(),
211 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0)),
212 root->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), b));
213 root->appendNewControlValue(
214 proc, Return, Origin(),
215 root->appendNew<Value>(
216 proc, BitOr, Origin(),
217 innerBitOr,
218 root->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), c)));
219
220 CHECK(compileAndRun<int>(proc, a) == ((a | b) | c));
221}

223void testBitOrImmBitOrArgImm32(int a, int b, int c)
224{
225 Procedure proc;
226 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
227 Value* innerBitOr = root->appendNew<Value>(
228 proc, BitOr, Origin(),
229 root->appendNew<Value>(
230 proc, Trunc, Origin(),
231 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0)),
232 root->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), c));
233 root->appendNewControlValue(
234 proc, Return, Origin(),
235 root->appendNew<Value>(
236 proc, BitOr, Origin(),
237 root->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), a),
238 innerBitOr));
239
240 CHECK(compileAndRun<int>(proc, b) == (a | (b | c)));
241}

243double bitOrDouble(double a, double b)
244{
245 return bitwise_cast<double>(bitwise_cast<uint64_t>(a) | bitwise_cast<uint64_t>(b));
246}
247
248void testBitOrArgDouble(double a)
249{
250 Procedure proc;
251 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
252 Value* argument = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), FPRInfo::argumentFPR0);
253 Value* result = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitOr, Origin(), argument, argument);
254 root->appendNewControlValue(proc, Return, Origin(), result);
255
256 CHECK(isIdentical(compileAndRun<double>(proc, a), bitOrDouble(a, a)));
257}

296{
297 return bitwise_cast<float>(bitwise_cast<uint32_t>(a) | bitwise_cast<uint32_t>(b));
298}

311}

355void testBitOrArgsFloatWithUselessDoubleConversion(float a, float b)
356{
357 Procedure proc;
358 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
359 Value* argumentA = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitwiseCast, Origin(),
360 root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Trunc, Origin(),
361 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0)));
362 Value* argumentB = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitwiseCast, Origin(),
363 root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Trunc, Origin(),
364 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR1)));
365 Value* argumentAasDouble = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, FloatToDouble, Origin(), argumentA);
366 Value* argumentBasDouble = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, FloatToDouble, Origin(), argumentB);
367 Value* doubleResult = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitOr, Origin(), argumentAasDouble, argumentBasDouble);
368 Value* floatResult = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, DoubleToFloat, Origin(), doubleResult);
369 root->appendNewControlValue(proc, Return, Origin(), floatResult);
370
371 double doubleA = a;
372 double doubleB = b;
373 float expected = static_cast<float>(bitOrDouble(doubleA, doubleB));
374 CHECK(isIdentical(compileAndRun<float>(proc, bitwise_cast<int32_t>(a), bitwise_cast<int32_t>(b)), expected));
375}

406void testBitXorAndAndArgs(int64_t a, int64_t b, int64_t c)
407{
408 // We want to check every possible ordering of arguments (to properly check every path in B3ReduceStrength):
409 // ((a & b) ^ (a & c))
410 // ((a & b) ^ (c & a))
411 // ((b & a) ^ (a & c))
412 // ((b & a) ^ (c & a))
413 for (int i = 0; i < 4; ++i) {
414 Procedure proc;
415 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
416 Value* argA = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0);
417 Value* argB = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR1);
418 Value* argC = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR2);
419 Value* andAB = i & 2 ? root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitAnd, Origin(), argA, argB)
420 : root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitAnd, Origin(), argB, argA);
421 Value* andAC = i & 1 ? root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitAnd, Origin(), argA, argC)
422 : root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitAnd, Origin(), argC, argA);
423 root->appendNewControlValue(
424 proc, Return, Origin(),
425 root->appendNew<Value>(
426 proc, BitXor, Origin(),
427 andAB,
428 andAC));
429
430 CHECK_EQ(compileAndRun<int64_t>(proc, a, b, c), ((a & b) ^ (a & c)));
431 }
432}

446 Value* argC = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Trunc, Origin(), root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR2));
447 Value* andAB = i & 2 ? root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitAnd, Origin(), argA, argB)

449 Value* andAC = i & 1 ? root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitAnd, Origin(), argA, argC)

462void testBitXorAndSameArgs(int64_t a, int64_t b)
463{
464 // We want to check every possible ordering of arguments (to properly check every path in B3ReduceStrength):
465 // ((a & b) ^ a)
466 // ((b & a) ^ a)
467 // (a ^ (a & b))
468 // (a ^ (b & a))
469 for (int i = 0; i < 4; ++i) {
470 Procedure proc;
471 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
472 Value* argA = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0);
473 Value* argB = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR1);
474 Value* andAB = i & 1 ? root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitAnd, Origin(), argA, argB)
475 : root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitAnd, Origin(), argB, argA);
476 Value* result = i & 2 ? root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitXor, Origin(), andAB, argA)
477 : root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitXor, Origin(), argA, andAB);
478 root->appendNewControlValue(proc, Return, Origin(), result);
479
480 CHECK_EQ(compileAndRun<int64_t>(proc, a, b), ((a & b) ^ a));
481 }
482}

794
795void testNotOnBooleanAndBranch32(int64_t a, int64_t b)
796{
797 Procedure proc;
798 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
799 BasicBlock* thenCase = proc.addBlock();
800 BasicBlock* elseCase = proc.addBlock();
801
802 Value* arg1 = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Trunc, Origin(),
803 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0));
804 Value* arg2 = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Trunc, Origin(),
805 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR1));
806 Value* argsAreEqual = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Equal, Origin(), arg1, arg2);
807 Value* argsAreNotEqual = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitXor, Origin(),
808 root->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), 1),
809 argsAreEqual);
810
811 root->appendNewControlValue(
812 proc, Branch, Origin(),
813 argsAreNotEqual,
814 FrequentedBlock(thenCase), FrequentedBlock(elseCase));
815
816 thenCase->appendNewControlValue(
817 proc, Return, Origin(),
818 thenCase->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), 42));
819
820 elseCase->appendNewControlValue(
821 proc, Return, Origin(),
822 elseCase->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), -42));
823
824 int32_t expectedValue = (a != b) ? 42 : -42;
825 CHECK(compileAndRun<int32_t>(proc, a, b) == expectedValue);
826}
827
828void testBitNotOnBooleanAndBranch32(int64_t a, int64_t b)
829{
830 Procedure proc;
831 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
832 BasicBlock* thenCase = proc.addBlock();
833 BasicBlock* elseCase = proc.addBlock();
834
835 Value* arg1 = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Trunc, Origin(),
836 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0));
837 Value* arg2 = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Trunc, Origin(),
838 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR1));
839 Value* argsAreEqual = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Equal, Origin(), arg1, arg2);
840 Value* bitNotArgsAreEqual = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitXor, Origin(),
841 root->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), -1),
842 argsAreEqual);
843
844 root->appendNewControlValue(proc, Branch, Origin(),
845 bitNotArgsAreEqual, FrequentedBlock(thenCase), FrequentedBlock(elseCase));
846
847 thenCase->appendNewControlValue(proc, Return, Origin(),
848 thenCase->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), 42));
849
850 elseCase->appendNewControlValue(proc, Return, Origin(),
851 elseCase->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), -42));
852
853 static constexpr int32_t expectedValue = 42;
854 CHECK(compileAndRun<int32_t>(proc, a, b) == expectedValue);
855}

1208 proc, ZShr, Origin(),
1209 root->appendNew<Value>(
1210 proc, Trunc, Origin(),
1211 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0)),
1212 root->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), b)));
1213
1214 CHECK(compileAndRun<uint32_t>(proc, a) == (a >> b));
1215}
1216
1217template<typename IntegerType>
1218static unsigned countLeadingZero(IntegerType value)
1219{
1220 unsigned bitCount = sizeof(IntegerType) * 8;
1221 if (!value)
1222 return bitCount;
1223
1224 unsigned counter = 0;
1225 while (!(static_cast<uint64_t>(value) & (1l << (bitCount - 1)))) {
1226 value <<= 1;
1227 ++counter;
1228 }
1229 return counter;
1230}

1240}

1888{
1889#if CPU(X86) || CPU(X86_64)
1890 double result;
1891 asm ("sqrtsd %1, %0" : "=x"(result) : "x"(value));
1892 return result;
1893#else
1894 return sqrt(value);
1895#endif
1896}

2051
2052void testCompareFloatToDoubleThroughPhi(float a, float b)
2053{
2054 Procedure proc;
2055 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
2056 BasicBlock* thenCase = proc.addBlock();
2057 BasicBlock* elseCase = proc.addBlock();
2058 BasicBlock* tail = proc.addBlock();
2059
2060 Value* condition = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0);
2061
2062 Value* arg1As32 = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Trunc, Origin(),
2063 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR1));
2064 Value* arg1Float = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitwiseCast, Origin(), arg1As32);
2065 Value* arg1AsDouble = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, FloatToDouble, Origin(), arg1Float);
2066
2067 Value* arg2AsDouble = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), FPRInfo::argumentFPR0);
2068 Value* arg2AsFloat = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, DoubleToFloat, Origin(), arg2AsDouble);
2069 Value* arg2AsFRoundedDouble = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, FloatToDouble, Origin(), arg2AsFloat);
2070
2071 root->appendNewControlValue(
2072 proc, Branch, Origin(),
2073 condition,
2074 FrequentedBlock(thenCase), FrequentedBlock(elseCase));
2075
2076 UpsilonValue* thenValue = thenCase->appendNew<UpsilonValue>(proc, Origin(), arg1AsDouble);
2077 thenCase->appendNewControlValue(proc, Jump, Origin(), FrequentedBlock(tail));
2078
2079 Value* elseConst = elseCase->appendNew<ConstDoubleValue>(proc, Origin(), 0.);
2080 UpsilonValue* elseValue = elseCase->appendNew<UpsilonValue>(proc, Origin(), elseConst);
2081 elseCase->appendNewControlValue(proc, Jump, Origin(), FrequentedBlock(tail));
2082
2083 Value* doubleInput = tail->appendNew<Value>(proc, Phi, Double, Origin());
2084 thenValue->setPhi(doubleInput);
2085 elseValue->setPhi(doubleInput);
2086 Value* equal = tail->appendNew<Value>(proc, Equal, Origin(), doubleInput, arg2AsFRoundedDouble);
2087 tail->appendNewControlValue(proc, Return, Origin(), equal);
2088
2089 auto code = compileProc(proc);
2090 int32_t integerA = bitwise_cast<int32_t>(a);
2091 double doubleB = b;
2092 CHECK(invoke<int64_t>(*code, 1, integerA, doubleB) == (a == b));
2093 CHECK(invoke<int64_t>(*code, 0, integerA, doubleB) == (b == 0));
2094}
2095
2096void testDoubleToFloatThroughPhi(float value)
2097{
2098 // Simple case of:
2099 // if (a) {
2100 // x = DoubleAdd(a, b)
2101 // else
2102 // x = DoubleAdd(a, c)
2103 // DoubleToFloat(x)
2104 //
2105 // Both Adds can be converted to float add.
2106 Procedure proc;
2107 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
2108 BasicBlock* thenCase = proc.addBlock();
2109 BasicBlock* elseCase = proc.addBlock();
2110 BasicBlock* tail = proc.addBlock();
2111
2112 Value* condition = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0);
2113 Value* argument32 = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Trunc, Origin(),
2114 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR1));
2115 Value* floatValue = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitwiseCast, Origin(), argument32);
2116 Value* argAsDouble = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, FloatToDouble, Origin(), floatValue);
2117
2118 root->appendNewControlValue(
2119 proc, Branch, Origin(),
2120 condition,
2121 FrequentedBlock(thenCase), FrequentedBlock(elseCase));
2122
2123 Value* postitiveConst = thenCase->appendNew<ConstDoubleValue>(proc, Origin(), 42.5f);
2124 Value* thenAdd = thenCase->appendNew<Value>(proc, Add, Origin(), argAsDouble, postitiveConst);
2125 UpsilonValue* thenValue = thenCase->appendNew<UpsilonValue>(proc, Origin(), thenAdd);
2126 thenCase->appendNewControlValue(proc, Jump, Origin(), FrequentedBlock(tail));
2127
2128 Value* elseConst = elseCase->appendNew<ConstDoubleValue>(proc, Origin(), M_PI);
2129 UpsilonValue* elseValue = elseCase->appendNew<UpsilonValue>(proc, Origin(), elseConst);
2130 elseCase->appendNewControlValue(proc, Jump, Origin(), FrequentedBlock(tail));
2131
2132 Value* doubleInput = tail->appendNew<Value>(proc, Phi, Double, Origin());
2133 thenValue->setPhi(doubleInput);
2134 elseValue->setPhi(doubleInput);
2135 Value* floatResult = tail->appendNew<Value>(proc, DoubleToFloat, Origin(), doubleInput);
2136 tail->appendNewControlValue(proc, Return, Origin(), floatResult);
2137
2138 auto code = compileProc(proc);
2139 CHECK(isIdentical(invoke<float>(*code, 1, bitwise_cast<int32_t>(value)), value + 42.5f));
2140 CHECK(isIdentical(invoke<float>(*code, 0, bitwise_cast<int32_t>(value)), static_cast<float>(M_PI)));
2141}
2142
2143void testReduceFloatToDoubleValidates()
2144{
2145 // Simple case of:
2146 // f = DoubleToFloat(Bitcast(argGPR0))
2147 // if (a) {
2148 // x = FloatConst()
2149 // else
2150 // x = FloatConst()
2151 // p = Phi(x)
2152 // a = Mul(p, p)
2153 // b = Add(a, f)
2154 // c = Add(p, b)
2155 // Return(c)
2156 //
2157 // This should not crash in the validator after ReduceFloatToDouble.
2158 Procedure proc;
2159 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
2160 BasicBlock* thenCase = proc.addBlock();
2161 BasicBlock* elseCase = proc.addBlock();
2162 BasicBlock* tail = proc.addBlock();
2163
2164 Value* condition = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0);
2165 Value* thingy = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitwiseCast, Origin(), condition);
2166 thingy = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, DoubleToFloat, Origin(), thingy); // Make the phase think it has work to do.
2167 root->appendNewControlValue(
2168 proc, Branch, Origin(),
2169 condition,
2170 FrequentedBlock(thenCase), FrequentedBlock(elseCase));
2171
2172 UpsilonValue* thenValue = thenCase->appendNew<UpsilonValue>(proc, Origin(),
2173 thenCase->appendNew<ConstFloatValue>(proc, Origin(), 11.5));
2174 thenCase->appendNewControlValue(proc, Jump, Origin(), FrequentedBlock(tail));
2175
2176 UpsilonValue* elseValue = elseCase->appendNew<UpsilonValue>(proc, Origin(),
2177 elseCase->appendNew<ConstFloatValue>(proc, Origin(), 10.5));
2178 elseCase->appendNewControlValue(proc, Jump, Origin(), FrequentedBlock(tail));
2179
2180 Value* phi = tail->appendNew<Value>(proc, Phi, Float, Origin());
2181 thenValue->setPhi(phi);
2182 elseValue->setPhi(phi);
2183 Value* result = tail->appendNew<Value>(proc, Mul, Origin(),
2184 phi, phi);
2185 result = tail->appendNew<Value>(proc, Add, Origin(),
2186 result,
2187 thingy);
2188 result = tail->appendNew<Value>(proc, Add, Origin(),
2189 phi,
2190 result);
2191 tail->appendNewControlValue(proc, Return, Origin(), result);
2192
2193 auto code = compileProc(proc);
2194 CHECK(isIdentical(invoke<float>(*code, 1), 11.5f * 11.5f + static_cast<float>(bitwise_cast<double>(static_cast<uint64_t>(1))) + 11.5f));
2195 CHECK(isIdentical(invoke<float>(*code, 0), 10.5f * 10.5f + static_cast<float>(bitwise_cast<double>(static_cast<uint64_t>(0))) + 10.5f));
2196}
2197
2198void testDoubleProducerPhiToFloatConversion(float value)
2199{
2200 Procedure proc;
2201 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
2202 BasicBlock* thenCase = proc.addBlock();
2203 BasicBlock* elseCase = proc.addBlock();
2204 BasicBlock* tail = proc.addBlock();
2205
2206 Value* condition = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0);
2207 Value* argument32 = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Trunc, Origin(),
2208 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR1));
2209 Value* floatValue = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitwiseCast, Origin(), argument32);
2210
2211 root->appendNewControlValue(
2212 proc, Branch, Origin(),
2213 condition,
2214 FrequentedBlock(thenCase), FrequentedBlock(elseCase));
2215
2216 Value* asDouble = thenCase->appendNew<Value>(proc, FloatToDouble, Origin(), floatValue);
2217 UpsilonValue* thenValue = thenCase->appendNew<UpsilonValue>(proc, Origin(), asDouble);
2218 thenCase->appendNewControlValue(proc, Jump, Origin(), FrequentedBlock(tail));
2219
2220 Value* constDouble = elseCase->appendNew<ConstDoubleValue>(proc, Origin(), 42.5);
2221 UpsilonValue* elseValue = elseCase->appendNew<UpsilonValue>(proc, Origin(), constDouble);
2222 elseCase->appendNewControlValue(proc, Jump, Origin(), FrequentedBlock(tail));
2223
2224 Value* doubleInput = tail->appendNew<Value>(proc, Phi, Double, Origin());
2225 thenValue->setPhi(doubleInput);
2226 elseValue->setPhi(doubleInput);
2227
2228 Value* argAsDoubleAgain = tail->appendNew<Value>(proc, FloatToDouble, Origin(), floatValue);
2229 Value* finalAdd = tail->appendNew<Value>(proc, Add, Origin(), doubleInput, argAsDoubleAgain);
2230 Value* floatResult = tail->appendNew<Value>(proc, DoubleToFloat, Origin(), finalAdd);
2231 tail->appendNewControlValue(proc, Return, Origin(), floatResult);
2232
2233 auto code = compileProc(proc);
2234 CHECK(isIdentical(invoke<float>(*code, 1, bitwise_cast<int32_t>(value)), value + value));
2235 CHECK(isIdentical(invoke<float>(*code, 0, bitwise_cast<int32_t>(value)), 42.5f + value));
2236}
2237
2238void testDoubleProducerPhiToFloatConversionWithDoubleConsumer(float value)
2239{
2240 // In this case, the Upsilon-Phi effectively contains a Float value, but it is used
2241 // as a Float and as a Double.
2242 Procedure proc;
2243 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
2244 BasicBlock* thenCase = proc.addBlock();
2245 BasicBlock* elseCase = proc.addBlock();
2246 BasicBlock* tail = proc.addBlock();
2247
2248 Value* condition = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0);
2249 Value* argument32 = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Trunc, Origin(),
2250 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR1));
2251 Value* floatValue = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitwiseCast, Origin(), argument32);
2252
2253 root->appendNewControlValue(
2254 proc, Branch, Origin(),
2255 condition,
2256 FrequentedBlock(thenCase), FrequentedBlock(elseCase));
2257
2258 Value* asDouble = thenCase->appendNew<Value>(proc, FloatToDouble, Origin(), floatValue);
2259 UpsilonValue* thenValue = thenCase->appendNew<UpsilonValue>(proc, Origin(), asDouble);
2260 thenCase->appendNewControlValue(proc, Jump, Origin(), FrequentedBlock(tail));
2261
2262 Value* constDouble = elseCase->appendNew<ConstDoubleValue>(proc, Origin(), 42.5);
2263 UpsilonValue* elseValue = elseCase->appendNew<UpsilonValue>(proc, Origin(), constDouble);
2264 elseCase->appendNewControlValue(proc, Jump, Origin(), FrequentedBlock(tail));
2265
2266 Value* doubleInput = tail->appendNew<Value>(proc, Phi, Double, Origin());
2267 thenValue->setPhi(doubleInput);
2268 elseValue->setPhi(doubleInput);
2269
2270 Value* argAsDoubleAgain = tail->appendNew<Value>(proc, FloatToDouble, Origin(), floatValue);
2271 Value* floatAdd = tail->appendNew<Value>(proc, Add, Origin(), doubleInput, argAsDoubleAgain);
2272
2273 // FRound.
2274 Value* floatResult = tail->appendNew<Value>(proc, DoubleToFloat, Origin(), floatAdd);
2275 Value* doubleResult = tail->appendNew<Value>(proc, FloatToDouble, Origin(), floatResult);
2276
2277 // This one *cannot* be eliminated
2278 Value* doubleAdd = tail->appendNew<Value>(proc, Add, Origin(), doubleInput, doubleResult);
2279
2280 tail->appendNewControlValue(proc, Return, Origin(), doubleAdd);
2281
2282 auto code = compileProc(proc);
2283 CHECK(isIdentical(invoke<double>(*code, 1, bitwise_cast<int32_t>(value)), (value + value) + static_cast<double>(value)));
2284 CHECK(isIdentical(invoke<double>(*code, 0, bitwise_cast<int32_t>(value)), static_cast<double>((42.5f + value) + 42.5f)));
2285}

2287void testDoubleProducerPhiWithNonFloatConst(float value, double constValue)
2288{
2289 Procedure proc;
2290 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
2291 BasicBlock* thenCase = proc.addBlock();
2292 BasicBlock* elseCase = proc.addBlock();
2293 BasicBlock* tail = proc.addBlock();
2294
2295 Value* condition = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0);
2296 Value* argument32 = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Trunc, Origin(),
2297 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR1));
2298 Value* floatValue = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitwiseCast, Origin(), argument32);
2299
2300 root->appendNewControlValue(
2301 proc, Branch, Origin(),
2302 condition,
2303 FrequentedBlock(thenCase), FrequentedBlock(elseCase));
2304
2305 Value* asDouble = thenCase->appendNew<Value>(proc, FloatToDouble, Origin(), floatValue);
2306 UpsilonValue* thenValue = thenCase->appendNew<UpsilonValue>(proc, Origin(), asDouble);
2307 thenCase->appendNewControlValue(proc, Jump, Origin(), FrequentedBlock(tail));
2308
2309 Value* constDouble = elseCase->appendNew<ConstDoubleValue>(proc, Origin(), constValue);
2310 UpsilonValue* elseValue = elseCase->appendNew<UpsilonValue>(proc, Origin(), constDouble);
2311 elseCase->appendNewControlValue(proc, Jump, Origin(), FrequentedBlock(tail));
2312
2313 Value* doubleInput = tail->appendNew<Value>(proc, Phi, Double, Origin());
2314 thenValue->setPhi(doubleInput);
2315 elseValue->setPhi(doubleInput);
2316
2317 Value* argAsDoubleAgain = tail->appendNew<Value>(proc, FloatToDouble, Origin(), floatValue);
2318 Value* finalAdd = tail->appendNew<Value>(proc, Add, Origin(), doubleInput, argAsDoubleAgain);
2319 Value* floatResult = tail->appendNew<Value>(proc, DoubleToFloat, Origin(), finalAdd);
2320 tail->appendNewControlValue(proc, Return, Origin(), floatResult);
2321
2322 auto code = compileProc(proc);
2323 CHECK(isIdentical(invoke<float>(*code, 1, bitwise_cast<int32_t>(value)), value + value));
2324 CHECK(isIdentical(invoke<float>(*code, 0, bitwise_cast<int32_t>(value)), static_cast<float>(constValue + value)));
2325}

2946void testStore8Arg()
2947{
2948 { // Direct addressing.
2949 Procedure proc;

2951

2953 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0));
2954 Value* address = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR1);
2955

2957 root->appendNewControlValue(proc, Return, Origin(), value);
2958
2959 int8_t storage = 0;
2960 CHECK(compileAndRun<int64_t>(proc, 42, &storage) == 42);
2961 CHECK(storage == 42);
2962 }
2963
2964 { // Indexed addressing.
2965 Procedure proc;
2966 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
2967
2968 Value* value = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Trunc, Origin(),
2969 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0));

2973
2974 Value* baseDisplacement = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Add, Origin(), displacement, base);
2975 Value* address = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Add, Origin(), baseDisplacement, offset);
2976

2978 root->appendNewControlValue(proc, Return, Origin(), value);
2979
2980 int8_t storage = 0;
2981 CHECK(compileAndRun<int64_t>(proc, 42, &storage, 1) == 42);
2982 CHECK(storage == 42);
2983 }

3023
3024void testStorePartial8BitRegisterOnX86()
3025{
3026 Procedure proc;
3027 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
3028
3029 // We want to have this in ECX.
3030 Value* returnValue = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0);
3031
3032 // We want this suck in EDX.
3033 Value* whereToStore = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR1);
3034
3035 // The patch point is there to help us force the hand of the compiler.
3036 PatchpointValue* patchpoint = root->appendNew<PatchpointValue>(proc, Int32, Origin());
3037
3038 // For the value above to be materialized and give the allocator
3039 // a stronger insentive to name those register the way we need.
3040 patchpoint->append(ConstrainedValue(returnValue, ValueRep(GPRInfo::regT3)));
3041 patchpoint->append(ConstrainedValue(whereToStore, ValueRep(GPRInfo::regT2)));
3042
3043 // We'll produce EDI.
3044 patchpoint->resultConstraints = { ValueRep::reg(GPRInfo::regT6) };
3045
3046 // Give the allocator a good reason not to use any other register.
3047 RegisterSet clobberSet = RegisterSet::allGPRs();
3048 clobberSet.exclude(RegisterSet::stackRegisters());
3049 clobberSet.exclude(RegisterSet::reservedHardwareRegisters());
3050 clobberSet.clear(GPRInfo::regT3);
3051 clobberSet.clear(GPRInfo::regT2);
3052 clobberSet.clear(GPRInfo::regT6);
3053 patchpoint->clobberLate(clobberSet);
3054
3055 // Set EDI.
3056 patchpoint->setGenerator(
3057 [&] (CCallHelpers& jit, const StackmapGenerationParams& params) {
3058 AllowMacroScratchRegisterUsage allowScratch(jit);
3059 jit.xor64(params[0].gpr(), params[0].gpr());
3060 });
3061
3062 // If everything went well, we should have the big number in eax,
3063 // patchpoint == EDI and whereToStore = EDX.
3064 // Since EDI == 5, and AH = 5 on 8 bit store, this would go wrong
3065 // if we use X86 partial registers.
3066 root->appendNew<MemoryValue>(proc, Store8, Origin(), patchpoint, whereToStore);
3067
3068 root->appendNewControlValue(proc, Return, Origin(), returnValue);
3069
3070 int8_t storage = 0xff;
3071 CHECK(compileAndRun<int64_t>(proc, 0x12345678abcdef12, &storage) == 0x12345678abcdef12);
3072 CHECK(!storage);
3073}
